-- Delta-Galil Rises Most Since February 2011 on Accord
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-05-02T13:57:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/delta-galil-rises-most-in-two-months-on-acquisition-accord.html
(Corrects size and scope of the move from headline.)  Delta-Galil Industries Ltd. (DELT)  surged the
most in more than a year after the manufacturer of intimate
apparel signed an accord to buy Schiesser Group AG for 68
million euros ($90 million).  The  shares  advanced 6 percent, the most since February last
year, to 32.62 shekels at 10.22 a.m. in  Tel Aviv , giving the
company a market value of 767 million shekels ($202 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
